cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper presents a new method for enabling full-duplex communication in many-antenna systems, which involves digital transmit beamforming and cancellation of residual self-interference. This involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and signal processing techniques, making cs.IT the most likely category. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method using measurements from a 72-element antenna array in both indoor and outdoor environments. This involves networking and internet architecture concepts such as wireless communication and network protocols. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a new method for controlling self-interference in many-antenna systems, which involves digital beamforming and cancellation. This involves systems and control concepts such as feedback control and system optimization. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the performance of the proposed method in terms of signal quality and dynamic range, which are important factors in multimedia applications such as audio and video transmission. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper does not focus on hardware architecture, but the proposed method may have implications for the design of hardware architectures for many-antenna systems.
